    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
      <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Aink420-kilavi">kuṟitta paruvattu eytiya aṇittāka vanta talaimakaṉ paruvattāl aṇi koṇṭa puṟavai nōkkic colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">The hero, who had reached by the appointed season and who had come close [to her village]<note place="foot" xml:lang="en">I am note quite sure how to take <q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">aṇittu āka</hi></q> - a adverbial phrase literally meaning: "in such a way to be close", or something like that?</note>, having looked at the forest which had taken ornamentation becasue of the season, spoke [this].</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <lg xml:id="Aink420">        
<l>poṉṉeṉa malarnta koṉṟai maṇiyeṉat</l>
    <l>tēmpaṭu kāyā malarnta tōṉṟiyoṭu</l>
    <l>naṉṉala meytiṉai puṟavē niṉṉaik</l>
    <l>kāṇiya varutum yāmē</l>
    <l>vāṇuta larivaiyo ṭāynalam paṭarntē</l>
          </lg>
          <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The laburnum that has blossomed like gold,</l>        
<l>the ironwood full of nectar [that looks] like sapphire,</l>          
<l>and the Malabar glory lily that has blossomed --</l>
<l>O forest you have obtained great beauty.</l>
<l>I will come to see you with the woman with a bright forehead,</l>
<l>thinking about<note xml:lang="en" place="foot"><q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">paṭarntu</hi></q> has another meaning of 'to set out'.</note> [your] fine beauty.<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">In the final phrase -- <q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">āy nalam paṭarntu</hi></q> -- I am not sure whose fine beauty is in his mind. It could be either the forest's or the heroine's.</note></l>
</lg>
        </div>
      </body>
    </text>
